# NOTICE

This project (`privrepomap`) is an independent, clean-room reimplementation.
It was written from scratch and does not copy source code from the projects
below, but its **design** is derived from and inspired by them.

## Design attribution

- **RepoMapper** by Pete Davis (MIT License)
  https://github.com/pdavis68/RepoMapper
  The structural approach — tree-sitter tag extraction, a defs/refs graph,
  PageRank ranking, and token-budgeted map rendering — follows the design
  pioneered there.

- **Aider** by Paul Gauthier and contributors (Apache-2.0 License)
  https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider
  The original repo-map concept (PageRank over a code graph + `TreeContext`
  rendering via `grep-ast`) originates here.

## Bundled data

The `queries/` directory contains tree-sitter tags query files (`*.scm`).
These are redistributed from the tree-sitter language grammars and the
`tree-sitter-language-pack` / `tree-sitter-languages` collections, which are
made available under permissive (MIT-style) licenses by their respective
authors. They are data files, not source code of this project.

## Differences from the original

- Offline token estimation (no `tiktoken`, no network).
- Strict privacy: `.gitignore`-aware scanning, secret-file skipping, and
  regex redaction of secrets applied to all rendered output.
- No telemetry, no cloud sync, no embeddings / NL semantic search.
